-- Goldman Says Pacific Metals, Bridgestone May Have Best Returns This Year
-- B y   N o r i e   K u b o y a m a   a n d   T o s h i r o   H a s e g a w a
-- 2012-01-12T23:56:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-12/goldman-says-pacific-metals-bridgestone-may-have-best-returns-this-year.html
Goldman Sachs Group Inc. said
Pacific Metals Co. and  Bridgestone Corp. (5108)  are among Japanese
stocks that will rise the most this year as the market recovers
from its worst slide since 2008.  Pacific Metals may gain as much as 60 percent, while
Bridgestone may climb 55 percent, the investment bank said in a
note to clients yesterday, citing the spread between current and
target prices.  SKY Perfect JSAT Holdings Inc. (9412)  and  Sumitomo
Rubber Industries Ltd. (5110)  are among equities that will advance the
most in the long-term, according to the report.  To contact the reporters on this story:
